{
  "texts": [
    "There are also no red (human-generated text) data points above 76 words.",
    "Therefore, conclusions about lengths outside this range should be considered very preliminary.",
    "Some AI detection systems could only be used partially or not at all in this study because they required a minimum number of characters of input that exceeded the length of our stimuli.",
    "TurnItIn required a minimum of 300 words and OpenAI 1,000 characters; none of our text stimuli were long enough to meet these criteria.",
    "Zero required a minimum of 250 characters, and hence could only be used with 5 of the human-generated stimuli."
  ]
}